cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.ET, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents a new software tool for teaching logic based on natural deduction. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the tool is developed for undergraduate computer science students who are used to study and program concrete computer code in a programming language. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the tool is open source software developed in TypeScript / JavaScript and can be used directly in a browser without any further installation. 
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies) is relevant as the paper presents a new software tool that uses a proof assistant and formalization in Isabelle, which is an emerging technology in the field of computer science. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the relevance of the approach for other proof systems, which could include those used in AI research.
